-- Telespazio, Germany's DLR Will Run Galileo Satellite, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 2010-10-25T05:22:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/telespazio-germany-s-dlr-will-run-galileo-satellite-handelsblatt-reports.html
A Telespazio SpA and Deutsches
Zentrum fuer Luft- und Raumfahrt e.V. joint venture backed by
Deutsche Telekom AG will sign a contract to operate the European
Galileo satellite navigation system in Brussels tonight,
Handelsblatt said, citing an unidentified DLR spokesman.  European Union Industry Commissioner Antonio Tajani is
scheduled to announce the deal tomorrow, the German newspaper
reported. The European Space Agency wants the Galileo project to
begin service in 2014 and be completed in 2016, Handelsblatt
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nicholas Comfort at 
 ncomfort1@bloomberg.net  